page.title: 11JIMMY TARBUCK
page.content: The comedian and compere{Jimmy {Tarbuck}was born in Liverpool. He attended Rose Lane and Dovedale Schools moving to London permanently in September 1963. As a child, his ambition was to become a professional footballer and he played with many teams, the most famous being Brighton and Hove Albion. He started his stage career by recording two 'pop' songs and then he moved on to compering in clubs in London.He was 'spotted' in a club called the 'Two Eyes' in Old Compton Street. He then moved on to greater things, compering things like 'Winner Takes All' and live entertainment such as 'Live from Her Majesty's' and 'Saturday Night at the Palladium' He is married with 3 children and lives in a beautiful house in Kingston Vale.
